com.esri.mo2.util
Class MessageCentre

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.esri.mo2.util.MessageCentre
public class MessageCentre
extends Object

Provides a convenient central location to gather and disseminate messages. An application can register itself as a MessageListener and display the messages received in some appropriate manner. To make it easier for applications to pass messages at various "levels" of application code, there is a "singleton" MessageCentre object that can be accessed using the get() method. Messages can then be placed on the MessageCentre by using one of the log() methods.

log

public void log(Object source,
                String message,
                int level)
Logs a message with the MessageCentre. The MessageCentre will broadcast the message to all interested Listeners. Each message can have a priority "level" indicating the importance of the message. Several priority levels are defined in this class, but user-defined priorities are also possible

Parameters:
source - the object that initiated the message
message - the message to broadcast
level - the priority level
See Also:
INFO, WARN, ERROR
